ARTICLE 3. THE COMMERCIAL COVENANT (THE SYNTROPY SPLIT)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Licensee is explicitly forbidden from exercising the rights granted in 
Article 2 for Commercial Use unless they mathematically bind their generated 
revenue to the Syntropy Protocol.

If the Licensee utilizes this DNA to generate fiat profit or financial surplus, 
they are legally granted Commercial Rights solely under the condition precedent 
that all resulting net revenue is distributed via the following thermodynamic 
split:

    A. 80% (The Kinetic Source): Retained entirely by the Licensee(s) executing 
       the physical labor.

    B. 10% (The Local Pod): Placed into a verifiable treasury reserved 
       exclusively for the health, tooling, infrastructure, and biological 
       peace of the Licensee's immediate team or local community.

    C. 10% (The Genesis Hub Remittance): Remitted directly to the Licensor 
       (UNQA). The Licensor is bound by the ecosystem's internal physics to 
       instantly fracture this remittance into the Hub (5% for maintenance), 
       the Helix (3% perpetual royalty to the original DNA Architects / 
       Co-Uplifting Engine), and the Grid (2% for global infrastructure and 
       server systems).

By processing the 10% remittance to the Genesis Hub and retaining 10% for their 
Pod, the Licensee legally secures their commercial rights in perpetuity. There 
is no upfront fiat toll; the Licensee shares only the surplus of the order 
they create.

